    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Design &amp; Implementation of Efficient FFT Algorithm for OFDM Based Communication Systems</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Kamatham Harikrishna</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Implementation of Efficient FFT Algorithm<br />Communication Systems</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Jan-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">T0081</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">The objective of our thesis is propos ing a new Radix -2
2
Algorithm
a n d i t s utilization in Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiplexing (O F DM )
based communication system. The modified OFDM communication system
has been implemented and the Fixed Worldwide Interoperability for Microwave
Access (WiMAX) and Mobile WiMAX systems are redesigned for better results.
The design has been done in AGILENTâ€™s ADVANCED DESIGN SYSTEM
(ADS) software.
Our proposed work is impl ement ed with VERILOG Hardware
Description Language (VERILOG). The code is synthesized and targeted into
Xilinx Spartan3 Field Programmable Gate Array (FPGA). This FPGA, after
programming, acts as an Fas t Four i er Tr ans form ( FFT) module with the
proposed algorithm. This module now used in OFDM communication
system. The pe r fo rmanc e and impl ementat ion in OFDM systems is
discussed. Simulation results of implementation in OFDM are presented and
the results of the proposed algorithm are compared with similar implementation
using Radix-4 algorithm. A comparison of hardware requirement of Radix-22 Single
Path Delay Feedback (R2
2
SDF) and several other popular pipeline architectures is
made.
The improved OFDM modules can then be implemented in fixed and
mobile WiMAX communication systems which utilize Orthogonal Frequency-
Division Multiple Access (OFDMA) technique for their c ommu n i c a t i o n . The
advantages, performance, and timing of the communication modules after
vi
implementation of the proposed technique are then discussed towards the end,
giving a scope for the manufacturing of efficient WiMAX communication
modules. A comparison is also made for the implementation o f the fixed and
mobile WiMAX, with the proposed architecture and that of the Radix -4
architecture. The comparison clearly indicates that the WiMAX with the proposed
architecture is efficient than the other implementation.
The outcome of this work has several potential applications in the field of
communication systems. This efficient OFDM communication module, after its
physical implementation, can be effectively utilized in the manufacturing of the
Fixed and Mobile WiMAX communication systems as discussed in this work.
Further, the implementation can also be extended to any other communication
standards that use OFDM technique in the architecture.</td></tr>
